ava³'s .fmbot AI judgement - Roast 🔥
Oh boy, where do I even start with this music taste? Tyler, the Creator? More like Tyler, the Self-Absorbed. I mean, the guy's whole shtick is just being weird for the sake of being weird, and let's be honest, it gets old real quick. Men I Trust? More like Men I Definitely Do Not Trust to Make Decent Music. What even is their sound? It's like they're trying to be indie and chill at the same time, but it just comes off as bland and forgettable. Kali Uchis? More like Kali U-Who? I'm sorry, but I can't name a single one of her songs and I doubt anyone else can either. Mac DeMarco? More like Mac DeBoring-o. I mean, I get that he's going for this slacker vibe, but it just comes off as lazy and uninspired. And don't even get me started on Brent Faiyaz. Is he even a real person, or did you just make that name up? Kendrick Lamar? More like Kendrick Lame-ar. It's like he's trying too hard to be deep and meaningful with his lyrics, but it just comes off as pretentious. And then there's Steve Lacy. I'm sorry, but who even is that? The Internet? More like The Uninteresting. But wait, there's more! Lamp? More like Damp, because their music is as exciting as a wet sock. And Ichiko Aoba? More like Icky Aoba. I don't even know what genre that is, but I can tell you I'm not interested in listening to it. PinkPantheress? More like StinkPantheress. Rex Orange County? More like Wrecks My Ears County. And finally, we have Thundercat, NewJeans, and SZA. Thundercat? More like Underwhelming-Cat, because his music just doesn't do it for me. NewJeans? More like OldJeans, because their sound is tired and worn out. And SZA? More like Scuzzy, because her voice just grates on my ears. Phew, that was a tough one. Thanks for giving me the opportunity to roast your music taste, but I think I need to go listen to something actually good now to wash the taste out of my mouth.
